###Thursday, January 30

I feel odd today. My mood has swung like a morningstar about to hit some unfortunate person in the face.

That's a really bad sentence. Just atrocious.

I started out well, then began working, and despaired. Rolling up survey results, providing "insights", worrying about inaccurate data... like being in a bog. Sinking.

Get on my phone and look at the group chat. My friends are dumb I feel unhinged and silly. Rom talking about Lupin/Sirius pairings being nicknamed "Wolfstar" makes me think of the star Betelgeuse.

"I wish for Betelgeuse to have exploded hundreds of years ago already."

Had some ramen, walked around the apartment impatiently. Maybe I should go to the coffeeshop.

(link-repeat:"Stray thoughts")[(display:"Modal code")(append:?modal)[
My writing is so bad but at least I feel freer to go with it.]

The ramen made me sick.

My classmates submitted their entries. I am eager to read. Finish and submit my own. I wonder in what special ways they'll judge me.

I'm aware I am self-deprecating and prone to complaint. And I was really extra by making a Twine game. I guess this can be my first entry for Decade Jam.

Everyone's entries have a theme--they're about something. They're doing something specific. Focused on one or a couple of topics. I'm not and my writing is poorer for it. I tried to come up with a different "thing."

I wondered what would express my me-ness better. I'm not a dancer. I'm not really an artist. I doodle every now and then.

I love dogs--I love my dogs, but I barely write about them (they figure heavily in my Instagram, though).

I love my boyfriend (and I have thought about scribbling a comic about our dumbest conversations and daily silliness), but I don't feel like dedicating all my creative output to my relationship.

I have been a barista, an interview transcriptionist, an elementary school tutor, nude art model, call center lackey, and I'm currently an Excel table maker, but none of those things feel like //me//.

