<br>

So I watched this GDC lecture from last year about cursed problems in gaming that I found fascinating. Cursed problems are simply conflicts in the premises of a game.

So, for example, the Quarterback Problem, an issue that happens in cooperative games when one person takes over and starts telling everyone what to do






